# to [[bend]]; to make bent
#: {{zh-x|彎腰|to bend over}}
# {{†}} to [[draw]] a [[bow]]
# [[bent]]; [[curved]]; [[crooked]]; [[arched]]
#: {{zh-x|彎曲|bent}}
#: {{zh-x|彎路|curved road}}
# {{lb|zh|neologism|opposite of {{zh-l|*直|straight}}}} [[gay]]; [[homosexual]]
#: {{zh-x|彎男|gay man}}
#: {{zh-x|變 彎|to become gay}}
# a [[bend]]; [[turn]]; [[curve]]; [[crook]]
#: {{zh-x|彎子|a bend}}
#: {{zh-x|拐彎|to turn (at a corner)}}
# {{lb|zh|Chinese calligraphy}} a bend (such as in {{m|mul|㇉}}, {{m|mul|㇌}}, {{m|mul|㇟}}{{,}} or {{m|mul|㇠}})
# ({{zh-l|灣}})
## a bend in a [[river]]
## a bend in the [[coastline]]; [[bay]], [[gulf]]
# {{zh-classifier|[[bent]] objects, such as a quarter moon}}

{{ja-readings
|goon=えん<ゑん
|kanon=わん
|kun=ひ-く, ひきまかな-う
}}

{{ja-kanjitab|わん|yomi=on}}
From {{etyl|ltc|ja|sort=わん}} {{m|ltc|彎|tr=*quan}}. Compare modern {{etyl|cmn|-}} {{zh-l|彎|tr=wān}}.

Note that this character is replaced in modern Japanese by the simplified character {{m|ja|湾|tr=wan}}, rather than the simplified Chinese character {{m|zh|弯|tr=wān||bend, curve}}. The Japanese simplified version means {{m|en|bay}} or {{m|en|inlet}} when used on its own, but now also includes the {{m|en|bend}}, {{m|en|curve}} meanings when used in compounds.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-l|彎月}}, {{ja-l|湾月|わんげつ|wangetsu}}: a [[crescent]] [[moon]]
* {{ja-l|彎曲}}, {{ja-l|湾曲|わんきょく|wankyoku}}: a [[bend]], a [[curve]]
* {{ja-l|彎屈}}, {{ja-l|湾屈|わんくつ|wankutsu}}: [[bending]] over, [[stooping]]
* {{ja-l|彎珠|わんじゅ|wanju}}: alternate name for {{m|ja|袴葛|tr=hakamakazura}}, a kind of {{vern|orchid tree}}: {{taxlink|Bauhinia japonica|species|noshow=1}}
* {{ja-l|彎入}}, {{ja-l|湾入|わんにゅう|wannyū}}: an [[inlet]] or [[bay]] along a [[coast]]
{{der-bottom}}
